@cuttlefish <cite>Do you have any lighter Futura italics than extra-black?</cite>

The lightest natural italic futura font that I have is futura xtra blk, the closest I could do was have futura book, or futura light set at italics which is not the intended oblique.

@timd<cite>While Futura is more sporty than Copperplate it isn’t that far away from a generic sports font and italic or oblique is regularly used as a metaphor for motion/sporting – it isn’t necessarily a bad thing to use an obvious style.</cite>

But the xblk's are just a tad to much correct? Also what are other possibilities that would be distinctive yet corporate like?

I know I am in my own little world, but its ok. They know me here
